{"body": "Your desired example of:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\nPost.first(title: 'lol')\r\n```\r\n\r\nIsn't actually complete.  The problem is that `first` and `last` are meaningless without an order (and can actually return different results depending on the databases).  So your example should probably be:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\nPost.order(:id).first(title: 'lol')\r\n```\r\n\r\nI'm definitely in favor of this change, but I wanted to point out a nuance. :)", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4773383", "created_at": "2012-03-28T17:26:55Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5639#issuecomment-4773383", "updated_at": "2012-03-28T17:26:55Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5639, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tenderlove/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tenderlove/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tenderlove/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tenderlove", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tenderlove/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/tenderlove", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tenderlove/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/f29327647a9cff5c69618bae420792ea?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F7c78335a8924215ea5c22fda1aac7b75.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tenderlove/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tenderlove/received_events", "gravatar_id": "f29327647a9cff5c69618bae420792ea", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tenderlove/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "tenderlove", "type": "User", "id": 3124, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tenderlove/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523814d7bd3543c15100dc45"}, "id": 4773383, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5639"}
